firstTutor:
The goal is to move call cards to the
foundation. Stacking them by suit
from Aces to King. For example, A, 2, 3,
and so on.
fourthTutor:
The sorting order on each foundation
in the upper left corner is arranged
according to: A-2-3-...-Q-K
moveOneCardOfRank: Move 1 card of {{rank}} to the Foundation
moveOneCardOfRank1AndYCardsOfRank2: Move 1 cards of {{rank1}} and {{count2}} cards of {{rank2}} to the Foundation
moveOneCardOfSuit: Move 1 card of {{suit}} to the Foundation
moveOneCardOfSuit1AndYCardsOfSuit2: Move 1 cards of {{suit1}} and {{count2}} cards of {{suit2}} to the Foundation
moveOneCardsOfRank1AndOneCardOfRank2: Move 1 card of {{rank1}} and 1 card of {{rank2}} to the Foundation
moveOneCardsOfSuit1AndOneCardOfSuit2: Move 1 card of {{suit1}} and 1 card of {{suit2}} to the Foundation
moveRankOfSuitToFoundation: Move the {{rank}} of {{suit}} to the Foundation
moveXCardsOfRank: Move {{count}} cards of {{rank}} to the Foundation
moveXCardsOfRank1AndOneCardOfRank2: Move {{count1}} cards of {{rank1}} and 1 card of {{rank2}} to the Foundation
moveXCardsOfRank1AndYCardsOfRank2: Move {{count1}} cards of {{rank1}} and {{count2}} cards of {{rank2}} to the Foundation
moveXCardsOfSuit: Move {{count}} cards of {{suit}} to the Foundation
moveXCardsOfSuit1AndOneCardOfSuit2: Move {{count1}} cards of {{suit1}} and 1 card of {{suit2}} to the Foundation
moveXCardsOfSuit1AndYCardsOfSuit2: Move {{count1}} cards of {{suit1}} and {{count2}} cards of {{suit2}} to the Foundation
newSettings:
New settings will take effect

revealRankOfSuitToTableau: Move the {{rank}} of {{suit}} to the Tableau
secondTutor:
Cards can be moved from column to
column. In each column, the cards are
arranged in order from largest to
smallest. Alternating red and black.
thirdTutor:
If the card below can't be moved, just
click the card stock in the upper right
corner, and more cards will be
provided here to help you solve the
problem!
